## Summary of Security Improvements

| Area | Change | Why |
|---|---|---|
| Headers | `helmet()` | Defends against XSS, clickjacking, MIME sniffing |
| DoS | `express.json({ limit: '10kb' })` + `express-rate-limit` | Prevents payload & brute-force attacks |
| Input validation | `express-validator` on params/queries | Stops injection & type-coercion bugs |
| Error leakage | Centralized error handler | Avoids exposing stack traces |
| Data exposure | Removed email from `/users` | Principle of least privilege |
| Config | `process.env.PORT` | 12-factor config, no hardcoding |
| Reliability | `SIGTERM`/`SIGINT` handlers | Graceful deploys |
| 404 | Explicit handler | Consistent API contract |

